    "privileged_info_summary": "The task operates on Emoncms (OpenEnergyMonitor), an open-source energy monitoring system. The node 'pvbms' has four synthetic input channels: solar_w (initial value 2450W), battery_soc (68%), battery_charge_w (550W), and battery_discharge_w (0W). Data is generated locally via API POST requests during setup, not from a real/external dataset. Process ID 1 ('Log to Feed') saves data to time-series feeds, and Process ID 4 ('Power to kWh') converts instantaneous power to cumulative energy. The system runs at http://localhost with credentials admin/admin. The agent must create feeds, configure input process lists, and build a dashboard named 'Solar Storage Monitor' with at least 4 widgets. Success is verified by database state inspection (input process lists, feed counts, and dashboard existence).",
